# RAG-Based Mini Q&A System

A lightweight **Retrieval-Augmented Generation** system that answers questions strictly from a provided document — no hallucinations.

**Stack:** LangChain · OpenAI · FAISS · Python

---

## Architecture

```
Document (.txt / .pdf)
        │
        ▼  LangChain TextLoader / PyMuPDFLoader
┌────────────────────────────────┐
│  RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter │  ~1500 chars/chunk, 200 overlap
└───────────────┬────────────────┘
                │
                ▼  OpenAI text-embedding-3-small
┌────────────────────────────────┐
│      OpenAI Embeddings          │  1536-dim vectors
└───────────────┬────────────────┘
                │
                ▼
┌────────────────────────────────┐
│       FAISS Vector Store        │  cosine similarity search
└───────────────┬────────────────┘
                │  User Query (embedded on-the-fly)
                ▼  top-3 chunks retrieved
┌────────────────────────────────┐
│   LangChain RetrievalQA Chain   │
│   + Custom PromptTemplate       │  "Answer ONLY from context"
└───────────────┬────────────────┘
                │
                ▼  OpenAI gpt-3.5-turbo
           Final Answer
```

---

## Quick Start

### 1. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

For PDF support:
```bash
pip install pymupdf
```

### 2. Set your OpenAI API key

```bash
export OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."
```

Or pass it directly with `--api-key sk-...`

### 3. Run interactive Q&A

```bash
python rag_app.py data/company_policy.txt
```

### 4. Single query (non-interactive)

```bash
python rag_app.py data/company_policy.txt --query "How many leave days?"
```

### 5. Run batch test queries

```bash
python test_queries.py
```

---

## CLI Reference

```
python rag_app.py <document> [options]

Positional:
  document              Path to .txt or .pdf file

Options:
  --api-key    STR      OpenAI API key (or set OPENAI_API_KEY env var)
  --model      STR      OpenAI model (default: gpt-3.5-turbo)
  --chunk-size INT      Characters per chunk (default: 1500 ≈ 300 words)
  --overlap    INT      Overlap chars between chunks (default: 200)
  --top-k      INT      Number of chunks to retrieve (default: 3)
  --query      STR      Run a single query then exit
  --verbose             Show retrieved source chunks with each answer
  --no-cache            Rebuild FAISS index even if cached
```

