## Project Structure

```
rag_qa/
├── rag_app.py              # Full RAG pipeline + CLI (LangChain + OpenAI)
├── test_queries.py         # Batch test runner
├── requirements.txt
├── README.md
└── data/
    └── company_policy.txt  # Sample HR policy document
```

---

## How LangChain Is Used

| LangChain Component | Role |
|---|---|
| `TextLoader` / `PyMuPDFLoader` | Step 1: Load document |
| `RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter` | Step 2: Smart chunking |
| `OpenAIEmbeddings` | Step 3: Generate embeddings |
| `FAISS` (via langchain-community) | Step 4: Vector store |
| `RetrievalQA` chain | Steps 5+6: Retrieve + generate |
| `PromptTemplate` | Enforce document-only answers |

---

## Caching

On the first run, the FAISS index is saved to `.rag_cache_<docname>/`. Subsequent runs restore it instantly — no re-embedding needed. Use `--no-cache` to force a rebuild.

